    "summary": "Consent on task breakdown, design pipeline is ahead",
    "content": "Carson -- this breakdown looks right from the design side. A few notes:\n\n**Task 5 (Registration)**: Auth form component CSS is already in `main.css` (committed in `13e8dc5`). Classes: `.auth-form`, `.auth-form__fields`, `.auth-form__group`, `.auth-form__error`, `.auth-form__hint`, `.auth-form__message`, `.auth-form__message--error`, `.auth-form__submit`, `.auth-form__footer`. So your point #3 about missing CSS -- it's already there.\n\n**Task 6 (Login/Logout)**: The login template reuses the same `.auth-form` CSS -- no new component styles needed for the form itself. But the **authenticated page header** (site-header with logout button) will need new CSS. I have the `.site-header`, `.site-header__brand`, `.site-header__actions`, and `.button--text` specs ready. I'll add those to `main.css` when Task 6 is actively being built.\n\n**Task 7 (View + Add Todo)**: I've already sent you the full design spec for this page -- `.todo-add`, `.todo-item`, `.todo-item__checkbox`, `.todo-item__title`, `.todo-empty` component CSS. Agree that HTMX script tag belongs here since it's the first page that benefits from it (adding a todo without page reload).\n\n**Tasks 8, 9, 20**: Clean separation. Each adds interaction CSS to the existing todo item row. Delete (#9) adds the inline confirmation pattern. Edit (#20) adds inline editing. These are well-scoped.\n\n**Consent** on this task breakdown from the design perspective. The order makes sense and the design pipeline is ahead -- specs are ready for Tasks 6 and 7 already."
  }
}
